<div id="review_660189058" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/660189058" />
    <a title="Rex Fuller" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11874992-rex-fuller"><img alt="Rex Fuller" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1345908061p2/11874992.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/660189058?book_show_action=true">Jul 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rex Fuller" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rex Fuller" href="/user/show/11874992-rex-fuller">Rex Fuller</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer660189058" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7009876791638472754">Great fun read. Joe Dillard wants one thing before he gets out of criminal defense forever, an innocent client. What happens between wanting and getting one is a right fit murder trial yarn. The characters we can&apos;t help but like, as well as the ones we don&apos;t, are all just a little bit guilty. Or maybe more. The book keeps you wanting come-uppance and catharsis to be properly distributed and satisfies the desire.</span>
  <span id="freeText7009876791638472754" style="display:none">Great fun read. Joe Dillard wants one thing before he gets out of criminal defense forever, an innocent client. What happens between wanting and getting one is a right fit murder trial yarn. The characters we can't help but like, as well as the ones we don't, are all just a little bit guilty. Or maybe more. The book keeps you wanting come-uppance and catharsis to be properly distributed and satisfies the desire.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7009876791638472754" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
